{[%evp 0,17,26,27,32,-17,25,30,34,-3,10,-6,12,17,6,-8,7,27,31,29]} 1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. g3 g6 {this is Black's most solid continuation, and it transposes to the Symmetrical Gruenfeld.} 5. Bg2 Bg7 (5... dxc4 6. O-O Bg7 7. a4 {transposes to Unit 3.}) 6. O-O O-O (6... dxc4 7. a4 {also transposes to Unit 3.}) 7. Qb3 {is our recommendation, and now Black has three main continuations.} Qb6 {will be discussed in "Position 2" of this Unit.} (7... Nbd7 $6 {is not good because after} 8. cxd5 cxd5 9. Nc3 $14 {[%csl Rd7] Black's knight on d7 is misplaced in this 'Exchange Slav' structure. For instance, the engine's best move here is 9...Nb8, which speaks for itself.}) (7... e6 $6 {is not in the spirit of the position.} 8. Nc3 Nbd7 9. Rd1 $14) (7... dxc4 {will be discussed in "Position 1" of this Unit.}) (7... a5 {will be discussed in "Position 3" of this Unit.}) *

