{[%evp 0,31,25,29,17,-4,45,18,18,1,3,3,30,-1,0,4,10,-6,-14,0,14,11,29,8,6,9,5,5,-3,8,0,8,6,-14]} 1. d4 d5 2. c4 c6 3. Nf3 Nf6 4. g3 dxc4 5. Bg2 b5 6. O-O Bb7 7. Ne5 e6 8. b3 cxb3 9. axb3 Be7 10. Nc3 {[%cal Gc3b5] Black has different moves here.} Qb6 {Second most played option.} (10... O-O {was played by Tomashevsky against Eljanov, but after} 11. Nxb5 Nd5 12. Na3 {It is clear that White is better.} c5 {The game continued with 13.Bb2, but I think that} 13. dxc5 {is even stronger.} Bxc5 14. Bb2 Nd7 15. Nd3 Be7 16. Nc4 {[%csl Gb2,Gg2] Our pieces are much better, especially the bishops.} Bf6 17. Qd2 Bxb2 18. Qxb2 {You need to get used to these positions, it looks like equal material, structure is the same, but it is not easy to play with Black. Our pieces are very active, engine says it is +1 already.} Qe7 {looks logical, but now} 19. Qa3 $1 {Even in the endgame, the problems persist.} Qxa3 20. Rxa3 $16 {[%csl Ra7][%cal Gf1a1,Ya7a6,Yc4d6] Very difficult to the defend the pawn. So you see, this is a very nice way to put pressure.}) (10... Nd5 {is not a great move, because it gives the important e4 squares to our knight.} 11. Ne4 {[%csl Ge4]} Qb6 {was played in the game Adams-Merry, White played 12.Bb2, which is normal of course, but} 12. Nc5 $146 {was even stronger.} Bxc5 13. dxc5 Qxc5 {We give back the second pawn, but we play on the dark squares also.} 14. Nd3 Qb6 15. e4 $16 {[%csl Yc5,Re8][%cal Gc1e3,Ge3c5] Very difficult position for Black.}) 11. Bg5 {A good reply.} h6 (11... O-O 12. Ne4 $36 {[%csl Re7] Black has problems with the pin.}) (11... a5 {is possible, but we can also play waiting moves.} 12. e3 h6 {Sooner or later Black will play this and we can play similarly to what we have seen.} 13. Bxf6 gxf6 14. Nd3 $44 {[%csl Ya5,Ge3]}) 12. Bxf6 gxf6 {is logical.} (12... Bxf6 13. Ne4 {[%csl Gc5] Our knights are very stable in the center.} Be7 {[%csl Ge5,Gh6][%cal Rf7f6,Ye5g6] f6 is never possible, because of Ng6.} 14. f4 $14 {[%cal Gf4f5] Keep in mind, that when h6 happens, our knight on e5 is stronger.}) 13. Nd3 Nd7 (13... Qxd4 $2 14. Nxb5 $16) 14. e3 {Long term, Black has problems with this structure and the king especially.} f5 {is probably best.} (14... O-O 15. Qh5 $40 {[%csl Rg8]}) (14... c5 15. d5 $16 {[%csl Re6,Rf6,Rf7] Very important.}) 15. Qf3 {[%csl Rb7][%cal Rc6c5,Gf3b7] Strong move, preventing c5.} a5 (15... O-O {Whenever castle happens, White can play} 16. g4 $40 {Strong attack.}) 16. Rfc1 $44 {[%cal Gg3g4,Ye8g8] I don't want to say that White is better, engine will hold always, but from human point, it is more difficult to play with Black, and White's compensation is guaranteed.} *

