{[%evp 0,43,19,31,14,-14,-11,0,0,-14,14,14,-2,-3,26,16,8,13,11,14,5,5,43,-13,23,15,14,-2,8,-9,10,19,13,4,22,5,26,-13,40,-31,10,6,6,6,24,-4]} 1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. Nf3 d5 4. g3 Be7 5. Bg2 O-O 6. O-O c6 7. Qc2 Nbd7 8. Nbd2 b6 9. e4 Ba6 {This move is possible, but it's very rare, and it doesn't have a clear logic. If Black wants to play with Ba6, then it's much better for him to start with 7...b6 and Ba6 immediately.} 10. e5 Ne8 11. Re1 Rc8 12. cxd5 (12. h4 $5 {deserves attention.}) 12... cxd5 13. Qb1 Nb8 {[%cal Gb8c6] This is probably Black's best plan.} (13... Qc7 {Black's most common move. His idea is Qc2, but we are better after} 14. b4 $1 {Very important move: without it, Black's position is immediately fine.} Qc2 15. b5 $16) 14. Nf1 Nc6 15. Bd2 Nb4 16. Bc3 $14 *

